article.headline: New Hampshire 61, Army 47
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Freshman Blagoj Janev scored 20 points, half in the last 10 minutes, to rally New Hampshire past Army 61-47 Tuesday night. Trailing 28-26 at halftime, New Hampshire used a 9-0 run with 10:21 to play to take the lead for good at 48-42. Craig Walls had 13 points for the Wildcats (4-6), and Griffin Walker added nine rebounds. Marshall Jackson and Bill Mohr scored 11 points apiece for the Black Knights (3-6), while Matt Bell had 10 points and Amadou Adeniyi had nine rebounds.
